    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged and judged acceptable given that the ASTM F1717 protocol is a standardized regulatory test method and the model ensemble provides additional confidence. All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference <10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for the stated COU. Supporting methodology is described in the literature (see referencesIdentifier).",
